## 3. Find decreases to accounts receivable

Primary ways: **Collections from customers** (i.e. a "Paid" status for customer previously Unpaid)

But in this data, "Paid" sales are separate entries, not matching earlier "Unpaid" sales. Since there is no explicit cash receipt against accounts receivable, we assume AR is increased at each Unpaid sale but not reduced anywhere (as no subsequent receipts documented as "receive payment" for AR).

Thus, **AR only increases with above and NO decrease**.
